[115.437613, "i", "cat > BUGFIX_SUMMARY.txt << 'EOF'\n=== CHECKPOINT/RESUME BUG FIXES ===\n\nPROBLEM: Batch job would not properly resume from checkpoint after being killed.\nCheckpoint file existed but script would reprocess everything from the beginning.\n\nROOT CAUSES IDENTIFIED AND FIXED:\n\n1. BUFFER FLUSH BUG (Critical)\n   - Original: save_checkpoint() used open() without context manager\n   - Issue: Buffer not flushed to disk before crash, checkpoint file empty/incomplete\n   - Fix: Added 'with' context manager, explicit f.flush() and os.fsync()\n\n2. SEMANTIC MISMATCH BUG (Critical)\n   - Original: Saved batch_num (0-49) but named it 'last_line'\n   - Issue: Resume code skipped line_num < start_from, so batch 5 = skip 5 lines, not 5000\n   - Fix: Changed to track actual line numbers (0-50000) consistently\n\n3. DATA ACCUMULATION BUG (Critical)\n   - Original: Used 'INSERT OR REPLACE' which overwrites existing data\n   - Issue: On resume, previous progress was lost as categories were replaced\n   - Fix: Changed to 'INSERT OR IGNORE' + 'UPDA"]
[115.437725, "i", "TE' to accumulate values\n\nADDITIONAL IMPROVEMENTS:\n   - Added conn.commit() after each batch (not just at end)\n   - Ensures database is consistent at checkpoint boundaries\n\nTEST RESULTS:\n   ✓ Full run: 50,000 records processed correctly\n   ✓ Interrupted at 45,000 lines, resumed successfully\n   ✓ Final totals match expected: 50,000 records, 2,494,808.87 total value\n   ✓ No duplicate processing or data loss\n\nFILES MODIFIED:\n   - process.py (fixed version)\n   - process.py.bak (original backup)\nEOF\n"]
[115.437771, "o", "cat > BUGFIX_SUMMARY.txt << 'EOF'\r\n"]
